        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The peak flux density and polarization fraction are rough estimates, with the former being 50% of the flux density at 43 GHz and the latter being the same as that at 43 GHz. The integration time is set by the desire to achieve polarimetric calibration, coverage of a full rotation of the object, and a highly significant detection. The source will be unresolved regardless of the array configuration. The focus of the observations is continuum emission and we use the standard correlator setup for this. There are no timing constraints on the observation.</prj:justificationText>
